---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../styles/home.css';

// NOTE: Baseline / starting-template privacy policy drafted from the app's
// actual data footprint (Clerk auth, Stripe payments, PostHog analytics +
// error tracking, DigitalOcean hosting, TMDB/Jikan content metadata).
// Self-hosted so it can't lapse like the old iubenda link. Review before
// relying on it legally; refine with Termly- or lawyer-reviewed text when
// ready. Keep the sub-processor list in sync as you add services (e.g. Resend).

const title = 'Privacy Policy - ShowShowShow';
const description = 'Privacy Policy for ShowShowShow';
const appUrl = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_APP_URL || 'https://app.showshowshow.app';
const effectiveDate = 'June 29, 2026';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="page">
    <header class="nav">
      <div class="nav-container">
        <a class="brand" href="/">ShowShowShow</a>
        <div class="nav-menu">
          <nav class="nav-links">
            <a href="/">Home</a>
            <a href="/terms">Terms</a>
            <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
          </nav>
          <a class="btn primary nav-cta-btn" href="/#waitlist">Join waitlist</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="content">
      <main class="section">
        <div class="card legal">
          <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p class="legal-meta">Effective date: {effectiveDate}</p>

          <p>
            This Privacy Policy explains what information ShowShowShow (“we,” “us,” or “our”)
            collects when you use our website and app at <a href={appUrl}>{appUrl}</a> (the
            “Service”), how we use it, and the choices you have. By using the Service, you agree to
            this policy.
          </p>

          <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
          <p><strong>Account information.</strong> When you sign up, our authentication provider
            (Clerk) collects and stores information needed to create and secure your account, such
            as your email address and name, and — if you sign in with a third-party provider — basic
            profile details from that provider.</p>
          <p><strong>Content you create.</strong> We store the things you create in the Service,
            such as your library, lists, lineups, schedules, watch progress, ratings, and notes,
            so we can show them back to you.</p>
          <p><strong>Payment information.</strong> If you subscribe to a paid plan, payments are
            handled by our payment processor, Stripe. Stripe collects and processes your payment
            details directly; we receive limited billing information (such as a customer/subscription
            identifier and your subscription status) and <strong>do not store your full payment card
            number</strong>.</p>
          <p><strong>Usage &amp; technical data.</strong> We use a product-analytics and
            error-monitoring provider (PostHog) to understand how the Service is used and to diagnose
            problems. This may include events about how you interact with the Service, device and
            browser information, approximate location derived from your IP address, and error logs.</p>

          <h2>2. How we use information</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>to provide, operate, and maintain the Service;</li>
            <li>to authenticate you and keep your account secure;</li>
            <li>to process subscriptions and payments;</li>
            <li>to understand usage, fix bugs, and improve the Service;</li>
            <li>to communicate with you about your account or support requests; and</li>
            <li>to comply with legal obligations and enforce our Terms.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>3. Service providers we share data with</h2>
          <p>
            We don’t sell your personal information. We share data only with the providers we rely
            on to run the Service, and only as needed for them to perform their function:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Clerk</strong> — account authentication and management</li>
            <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — payment processing and subscription billing</li>
            <li><strong>PostHog</strong> — product analytics and error monitoring</li>
            <li><strong>DigitalOcean</strong> — application and database hosting</li>
            <li><strong>TMDB</strong> and <strong>Jikan / MyAnimeList</strong> — sources of title
              metadata (we send title search queries to retrieve show, movie, and anime
              information; we do not send them your personal account data)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We may also disclose information if required by law or to protect the rights, safety,
            and security of our users or the Service.</p>

          <h2>4. Cookies &amp; similar technologies</h2>
          <p>
            We and our providers use cookies and similar technologies to keep you signed in and to
            measure how the Service is used. You can control cookies through your browser settings,
            though some features may not work without them.
          </p>

          <h2>5. Data retention</h2>
          <p>
            We keep your information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide
            the Service. When you delete your account, we delete or anonymize your personal
            information, except where we need to retain it to meet legal, accounting, or security
            obligations.
          </p>

          <h2>6. Your rights &amp; choices</h2>
          <p>
            Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct, export, or delete
            your personal information, and to object to or restrict certain processing (for example,
            under the GDPR or CCPA). You can manage much of your information from your account
            settings, or contact us to exercise these rights. You can also stop processing at any
            time by deleting your account.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Data security</h2>
          <p>
            We use reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your information.
            However, no method of transmission or storage is completely secure, and we can’t
            guarantee absolute security.
          </p>

          <h2>8. International transfers</h2>
          <p>
            We and our providers may process and store information in countries other than your own.
            Where required, we take steps to ensure your information receives an adequate level of
            protection when transferred internationally.
          </p>

          <h2>9. Children’s privacy</h2>
          <p>
            The Service isn’t directed to children under 13, and we don’t knowingly collect personal
            information from them. If you believe a child has provided us personal information,
            please contact us and we’ll delete it.
          </p>

          <h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we’ll update the
            effective date above and, where appropriate, notify you.
          </p>

          <h2>11. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about your privacy or this policy? Email us at
            <a href="mailto:hello@showshowshow.app">hello@showshowshow.app</a>.
          </p>

          <div class="legal-back">
            <a class="btn ghost" href="/">Back to home</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .legal {
      max-width: 820px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      text-align: left;
      line-height: 1.65;
    }
    .legal h1 {
      margin: 0 0 8px;
      font-family: Sora, sans-serif;
    }
    .legal h2 {
      margin: 28px 0 8px;
      font-family: Sora, sans-serif;
      font-size: 1.15rem;
    }
    .legal p,
    .legal li {
      color: var(--soft-ink);
    }
    .legal ul {
      padding-left: 20px;
    }
    .legal li {
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }
    .legal-meta {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      opacity: 0.8;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }
    .legal-back {
      margin-top: 32px;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
